04/11/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Nine countries in Southeast Europe are holding a joint military exercise involving responses to terrorist strikes and major natural disasters, Albanian authorities announced Wednesday (3 November). Albania, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Macedonia, Romania, Slovenia and Turkey are taking part in the programme, called Southeast European Simulation. The drill, which continues through 12 November, was organised under NATO's Partnership for Peace programme. 
In other news, Ljubljana will be hosting the annual meeting of the Southeast Europe Defence Ministerial process, starting Friday. The defence ministers of the region will discuss activities and developments related to the South Eastern Europe Brigade and its budget. (AP, Bulgarian National Radio, Bulgarian Defence Ministry Web site - 03/11/04) 
